<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,871,1618]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,951,977]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species, as well as the following, belongs to the 
<emphasis box="[946,1105,952,977]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Mesoscutatus</emphasis>
- 
<typeStatus box="[1113,1165,952,978]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
phyletic lineage previously discussed, defined as a section of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[632,726,992,1017]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[632,726,992,1017]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pardo Alcaide, A." box="[775,1034,992,1018]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="55 - 88" refId="ref23711" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1954) Etudes sur les Meloidae. V. Les Mylabrini du Maroc et du Sahara occidental espagnol (Col. Meloidae). Bulletin de la Societe de Sciences naturelles et physiques du Maroc, 34, 55 - 88." type="journal article" year="1954">Pardo Alcaide (1954)</bibRefCitation>
, and characterized by a large and well defined fore area of the mesosternum. The most species of the diverse genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[1133,1227,1032,1057]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1133,1227,1032,1057]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have this 
<typeStatus box="[1352,1402,1032,1058]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
of mesosternum, and several groups of species can be singled out within this lineage.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,871,1618]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
In particular, the group of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[510,668,1112,1137]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duplicatus">
<emphasis box="[510,668,1112,1137]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. duplicatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Afrotropical complex which includes at least 5 species distributed in the East Africa and Arabian Peninsula, well characterized by the last male antennomere apically bifid (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Bologna, M. A." box="[328,500,1192,1218]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="375 - 457" refId="ref22718" refString="Bologna, M. A. (1990) Faunistica e zoogeografia dei Meloidae (Coleoptera) della Somalia. Biogeographia, (n. s.) 13, 375 - 457." type="journal article" year="1990">Bologna 1990</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[521,823,1192,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestuans">
<emphasis box="[521,661,1192,1217]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. aestuans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, J. C. F." box="[679,815,1192,1218]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref23620" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1845) Symbolae physicae seu icones et dscriptiones Insectorum que ex itinere per Africam borealem et Asiam occidentalem Fridericii Guilelmi Hemprich et Christiani Godofredi Ehrenberg medicinae et chirurgiae doctorum studio nova autillustrate redierunt. Insecta. Reumen, Berolini, 24 pp, 2 pls." type="book" year="1845">Klug, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(Arabian Peninsula, 
<collectingCountry box="[1076,1179,1192,1218]" name="Ethiopia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1192,1271,1192,1218]" name="Kenya" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1285,1386,1192,1218]" name="Somalia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Somalia</collectingCountry>
); 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1933)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1933" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andreinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. andreinii</emphasis>
(Pic, 1933)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[411,496,1232,1258]" name="Eritrea" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Eritrea</collectingCountry>
; this species needs confirmation); 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fairmaire, 1882)" baseAuthorityName="Fairmaire" baseAuthorityYear="1882" box="[902,1305,1232,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrostictus">
<emphasis box="[902,1090,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. argyrostictus</emphasis>
(Fairmaire, 1882)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1321,1423,1232,1258]" name="Somalia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Somalia</collectingCountry>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[151,466,1272,1298]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="duplicatus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. duplicatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, J. C. F." box="[324,459,1272,1298]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref23620" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1845) Symbolae physicae seu icones et dscriptiones Insectorum que ex itinere per Africam borealem et Asiam occidentalem Fridericii Guilelmi Hemprich et Christiani Godofredi Ehrenberg medicinae et chirurgiae doctorum studio nova autillustrate redierunt. Insecta. Reumen, Berolini, 24 pp, 2 pls." type="book" year="1845">Klug, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry box="[482,585,1272,1298]" name="Djibouti" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Djibouti</collectingCountry>
, Arabian Peninsula); 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug, 1845)" authorityName="Bologna &amp; Turco" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[837,1154,1272,1298]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scapularis">
<emphasis box="[837,995,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. scapularis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, J. C. F." box="[1011,1146,1272,1298]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref23620" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1845) Symbolae physicae seu icones et dscriptiones Insectorum que ex itinere per Africam borealem et Asiam occidentalem Fridericii Guilelmi Hemprich et Christiani Godofredi Ehrenberg medicinae et chirurgiae doctorum studio nova autillustrate redierunt. Insecta. Reumen, Berolini, 24 pp, 2 pls." type="book" year="1845">Klug, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(Arabian Peninsula).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,871,1618]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
In the MNHN collections, we examined the 
<typeStatus box="[736,786,1312,1338]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1909" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1909" box="[831,1214,1312,1338]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosissima">
<emphasis box="[831,1089,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Zonabris rugosissima</emphasis>
Pic, 1909
</taxonomicName>
, a species cited in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaszab, Z." box="[151,343,1352,1378]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="144 - 204" refId="ref23584" refString="Kaszab, Z. (1983) Insects of Saudi Arabia. Coleoptera: Fam. Meloidae - A synopsis of the Arabian Meloidae. Fauna of Saudi Arabia, 5, 144 - 204." type="journal article" year="1983">Kaszab’s (1983)</bibRefCitation>
synopsis without settlement as to its taxonomic status. The Hungarian specialist suggested a possible synonymy with “ 
<emphasis box="[457,733,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Voigts" authorityYear="1902" box="[457,613,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Decapotoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Decapotoma</taxonomicName>
” scabrata
</emphasis>
, a species belonging to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1817" box="[1137,1232,1392,1417]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1137,1232,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hycleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
discussed below. The 
<typeStatus box="[203,253,1432,1458]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
specimen has the following labels: a) “Arabia f. Mylabre”; “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[963,1066,1432,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestuans">
<emphasis box="[963,1066,1432,1457]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">aestuans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
var.” (handwritteen by M. Pic); “ 
<typeStatus box="[161,240,1472,1498]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">TYPE</typeStatus>
” (handwritteen by M. Pic); “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1909" box="[579,767,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosissima">
<emphasis box="[579,720,1472,1497]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">rugosissima</emphasis>
Pic
</taxonomicName>
” (handwritteen by M. Pic); “ 
<typeStatus box="[1104,1159,1472,1498]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">type</typeStatus>
” (red, printed); “ 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Gorrizia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestuans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Gorrizia aestuans</emphasis>
(Klug)
</taxonomicName>
, Pardo Alcaide det. 1967 (printed).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1436,871,1618]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
This new synonymy of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic, 1909" authorityName="Pic" authorityYear="1909" box="[484,863,1552,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Zonabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rugosissima">
<emphasis box="[484,742,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Zonabris rugosissima</emphasis>
Pic, 1909
</taxonomicName>
= 
<taxonomicName authority="(Klug, 1845)" baseAuthorityName="Klug" baseAuthorityYear="1845" box="[900,1272,1552,1578]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Hycleus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aestuans">
<emphasis box="[900,1106,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Hycleus aestuans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Klug, J. C. F." box="[1124,1263,1552,1578]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" refId="ref23620" refString="Klug, J. C. F. (1845) Symbolae physicae seu icones et dscriptiones Insectorum que ex itinere per Africam borealem et Asiam occidentalem Fridericii Guilelmi Hemprich et Christiani Godofredi Ehrenberg medicinae et chirurgiae doctorum studio nova autillustrate redierunt. Insecta. Reumen, Berolini, 24 pp, 2 pls." type="book" year="1845">Klug, 1845</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, confirms the Pardo Alcaide’s identification, never published, and clarifies the uncertain Kaszab’s citation (1983).
</paragraph>
